# PDO::FETCH_CLASS

You can map rows directly to objects of a specific class. Properties are set before the constructor is called.

```php
class User {
    public $name;
    public $email;
}

$stmt = $pdo->query('SELECT name, email FROM users');
$users = $stmt->fetchAll(PDO::FETCH_CLASS, 'User');
```

This is very handy for clean OOP code.
